Worried over the spate of abandoned projects across the country, Chief Executive Officer, Project Management Conference (PROMACOM) Taofeek Babayeju has hinted of plans to partner with the government on resuscitation of abandoned projects all over the country. PROMACOM boss, who spoke at a media briefing ahead of PROMACOM 10th anniversary coming up in November 2019 in Abuja, said, “The objective of the gathering, is to among other things address the challenges bedeviling effective project delivery across all sectors in the country. The conference is also aimed at creating awareness for the role of project management in national development, promoting project management practices, contributing to the establishment of project management as a profession in Nigeria and developing a vibrant project management specialist network.”